resources_ideas_theme_3: Tracking public money flows
---
resources_ideas_theme_3_text:

The [Open Contracting Partnership](https://www.open-contracting.org) and Hivos' [Open Up Contracting](https://www.openupcontracting.org/) websites provide lots of guidance and examples for people looking to do Open Data Day events focused on public procurement and spending. See also: the [Open Data Charter guide to using open data to combat corruption](https://open-data-charter.gitbook.io/open-up-guide-using-open-data-to-combat-corruption/).
---
resources_ideas_theme_4: Open mapping
---
resources_ideas_theme_4_text:

Find out more about open mapping via the [Mapbox](https://www.mapbox.com), [OpenStreetMap](https://www.openstreetmap.org/) and [Humanitarian OpenStreetMap](https://www.hotosm.org/) websites.

---
resources_ideas_theme_5: Data for equal development
---
resources_ideas_theme_5_text:

The [Centre for Humanitarian Data](https://data.humdata.org) has over 17,000 humanitarian open datasets available via the CKAN-powered portal at [data.humdata.org](https://data.humdata.org/) which may help to highlight key issues about equal development. You can also visit the [United Nations' Open SDG Data Hub](https://unstats-undesa.opendata.arcgis.com), the [World Bank Open Data portal](https://data.worldbank.org) or the large data harvesting portals like the [European Data Portal](https://data.europa.eu/en).

---
resources_ideas_theme_6: Ocean data for a thriving planet
---
resources_ideas_theme_6_text:

General ocean data portals include [EMODNet](https://emodnet.ec.europa.eu/en) and the [Pacific Data Hub](https://pacificdata.org/). For oceanographic data - seafloor maps, temperatures, currents - try the [International Oceanographic Data Exchange](https://uk-ioc.org/IODE) and [Schmidt Ocean Institute](https://schmidtocean.org/data/). For data on ocean wildlife try the [Ocean Biological Information System](https://obis.org/) the [Global Biological Information System](https://www.gbif.org/) and the [Ocean Tracking Network]( https://members.oceantrack.org/OTN/projects). [Global Fishing Watch](https://globalfishingwatch.org/datasets-and-code/) focuses on fishing, especially on the high seas and [Marine Traffic](https://www.marinetraffic.com/) shows all kinds of vessels.

